item.title: What is your: Toughest, chillest, weirdest, Catchiest and underrated tracks?
item.dc:creator: El1011
item.description:
A bit late to the party, but why not.

Toughest:

  • Honestly I actually have like a full LP’s worth of harder hitting tracks ive never released, but in terms of released stuff, this is it, My heaviest Auxy track: Untitled. It’s super short and one of my first auxy tracks i posted that wasn’t a BTC. It’s not super impressive in terms of quality, but i just threw the fattest basses on there that i could with the old original sounds and i still think it somewhat holds up.

Chillest:

  • I do have a few that i deep worthy of a “chill” title, but the one i think is the best would be my winter tourney entry Holiday. The challenge was to make a melody that revolved around a winter memory or something like that.

Weirdest:

  • Hands down Nuke It. I dont know when i got this or if i got the project from someone, but while clearing out old tracks i came across that one and just thought it was some weird af stuff. It’s not really a full track, more of a beat, but still. weird

Catchiest:

  • Although i literally have a track where i tried to channel Alan Walker to make, i dont think it’s my catchiest track. That one goes to The Comet. Something about that baseline that when i got all the tracks together just stuck in my head for a while and i kept replaying it.

Most underrated:

  • For this one though i do have a good number of tracks with very few plays, i’m only going to mention it if i think it’s quality. From just numbers, it’s Bittersweet with only 23 plays and it’s been out for over a year now. No likes either oof. I originally thought that it sounded ice cold and thought it’d do much better than it has. spoiler

Honorable mentions: (lot of these bare with me here)

  • An auxy tourney entry that i still feel is pretty fire even if it’s just the drop
  • Psychedelic and Loneliness are 2 tracks that are on the chill side, but are also tracks that are lowkey underrated to me just by the amount of interaction on them.
  • While not super high quality, I think this is one of the first Moombah track i’ve seen in Auxy or at least one of the few left since IVO/XAVIOR deleted most of his older stuff.

apologize if it seems like im just trying to plug myself in here hella much, but i tried to explain all my track choices, even if there were quite a few of them

item.title: What is your: Toughest, chillest, weirdest, Catchiest and underrated tracks?
item.dc:creator: Plhector
item.description:
Toughest:
Atmosfear — It was first attempt at trying to make a thrilling theme. I think it turned out okay.
Chillest:
Vintage Keys Edit — It’s basically an extended version of the vintage keys demo.
Weirdest:
Psycho — It’s the first song where I used 48th notes. I also had some polyrhythm changes. I “distorted” almost all the instruments I used so it’s very hectic.
Catchiest:
Night Club Showdown — It just has a really rhythmic bass and the chorus is really simple, but does the trick! Probably the song I’m most proud of and it’s also the song that has the most likes!
Underrated:
Melancholy Mix — I’m a fan of tango and I mixed it with a trap beat as a joke, but it turned out sounding really good so I decided to make the whole beat a trap beat.

item.title: What is your: Toughest, chillest, weirdest, Catchiest and underrated tracks?
item.dc:creator: HYDRANS
item.description:
To prevent this from becoming a self promo dump thread, why don’t people explain their choices more.

I’ll explain a bit more about my previous choices.

Toughest: I chose two non-Auxy songs for this category. The first one, motion, is a self released track that I posted a few months ago. The track is definitely a top choice because the drop is pretty unexpected and hits hard. The other choice, variable, is my first non-Auxy song that had an official release. It was released with Tesseract Records earlier in the year. I chose this one because the punchy drums along with the gritty bass and lead patterns make the drop very hard hitting.

Chillest: I chose my track hologram, which I released with Ridgeline back when I was using Auxy as my primary DAW. I still hadn’t found my niche yet and this track reflects some experimentation with the chill genre. I would have picked purple magic for this one but I personally like hologram more.

Weirdest: If you haven’t heard my music, I make some pretty weird and experimental stuff. Most of the stuff on my main SoundCloud page after February is really weird since I became more interested in the experimental bass genre at that time.

Catchiest: I chose Insomnia, my first label release with Auxy (and in general). The song was released with Frontier last August. You may notice that the track is very different from my current stuff. At that time, I was making more melodic EDM stuff, but I still used some experimentation in the track. The song is so catchy because I spent a long time perfecting the main melody until it was perfect.

Most underrated: My track monsoon season was released about a month ago as the debut single for an album I’m working on. The track is currently sitting just below 300 plays, which is one of the lowest tracks on my page. I was pretty proud of this track so I’m hoping the track will get more exposure once the full album is released.
